The recipe did not change in the version migration, a URL did not hash, or there is jinja2 syntax the bot cannot handle!

Please check the URLs in your recipe with version '0.7.2' to make sure they exist!

We also found the following errors:

 - could not hash URL template 'https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/pynng-{{ version }}.tar.gz'

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pynng" %}
{% set version = "0.7.2" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/pynng-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a9f86376cdccb6feaa6179e65d684387e86f89440ed6f1b918a4f0502523b83b
  patches:
    - fix-windows-builds.patch  # [win]

build:
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  skip: true  # [osx]

requirements:
  build:
    - cmake
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - ninja
    - make  # [unix]
  host:
    - cffi
    - pip
    - pytest-runner
    - python
  run:
    - cffi
    - python
    - sniffio

test:
  imports:
    - pynng
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/codypiersall/pynng
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: Python bindings for Nanomsg Next Generation.
  description: |
    Ergonomic bindings for nanomsg next generation (nng), in Python. pynng
    provides a nice interface on top of the full power of nng. nng, and
    therefore pynng, make it easy to communicate between processes on a
    single computer or computers across a network. This library is
    compatible with Python ≥ 3.5. nng is the rewriting of Nanomsg, which
    is the spiritual successor to ZeroMQ.
  doc_url: https://pynng.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/codypiersall/pynng

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jan-janssen
    - carlodri
